  "html": "<div class=\"fr-view\">\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">The conjugation of ない form</span></strong></p>\n<p>1) Group 1</p>\n<p>The preceding vowel of 「ない」 goes to [a] instead of [i].</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/e32/0b1/e94/Screen_Shot_2020-06-22_at_11.49.21.png\" style=\"width: 579px;\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dib fr-fil\" srcset=\"https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/e32/0b1/e94/Screen_Shot_2020-06-22_at_11.49.21.png?width=1920 1x, https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/e32/0b1/e94/Screen_Shot_2020-06-22_at_11.49.21.png?width=1920&amp;dpr=2 2x, https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/e32/0b1/e94/Screen_Shot_2020-06-22_at_11.49.21.png?width=1920&amp;dpr=3 3x\"></p>\n<p>In cases of 「います」, 「わない」 instead of 「あない」 is used. As explained before, this type of verbs has [w]. However, due to the phonetic restriction of the modern Japanese, [w] only appears before [a].</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/29f/58c/eb9/Screen_Shot_2020-06-22_at_11.49.26.png\" style=\"width: 581px;\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dib fr-fil\" srcset=\"https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/29f/58c/eb9/Screen_Shot_2020-06-22_at_11.49.26.png?width=1920 1x, https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/29f/58c/eb9/Screen_Shot_2020-06-22_at_11.49.26.png?width=1920&amp;dpr=2 2x, https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/29f/58c/eb9/Screen_Shot_2020-06-22_at_11.49.26.png?width=1920&amp;dpr=3 3x\"></p>\n<p>There is only one exception in the group 1 「ない」 forms. That is for the verb 「あります」and 「ない」. 「ない」becomes the form of this verb. This is because「ない」is an い adjective of inexistence. You will find more information on 「ない」 in Day 34 lesson.</p>\n<p>2) Group 2 </p>\n<p>As often is the case for verbs of the 2nd group, the only substitution necessary to conjugate「ない」 form is that you swap「ます」for 「な い」  instead.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/b1e/0c2/86d/Screen_Shot_2020-06-22_at_11.49.18.png\" style=\"width: 578px;\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dib fr-fil\" srcset=\"https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/b1e/0c2/86d/Screen_Shot_2020-06-22_at_11.49.18.png?width=1920 1x, https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/b1e/0c2/86d/Screen_Shot_2020-06-22_at_11.49.18.png?width=1920&amp;dpr=2 2x, https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/b1e/0c2/86d/Screen_Shot_2020-06-22_at_11.49.18.png?width=1920&amp;dpr=3 3x\"></p>\n<p>3)  Group 3</p>\n<p>The same principle as group 2 is applicable to 「します」 of the 3rd group: します/しない, while「きま す」 has an exceptional conjugation and becomes 「こない」.</p>\n</div>",
